It fails on `memline.c` on line 1276:

```c
  if (fname != NULL) {
#ifdef HAVE_READLINK
    // Expand symlink in the file name, because the swapfile is created
    // with the actual file instead of with the symlink.
    if (resolve_symlink(fname, fname_buf) == OK) {
      fname_res = fname_buf;
    } else
#endif  // <-- right here
    fname_res = fname;
  }
```

I guess we can disable the warning on that line only, but the check isn't really needed to begin with since uncrustify already adds braces around all statements. I don't mind either way, what do you prefer?

